Nah, what comes to mind at the moment (I've probably seen better, but too tired to think):<br>
<br>
Eastern:<br>
'Hero' and 'Crouching tiger, hidden dragon' comes to mind.<br>
I'm a real sucker for the beauty of Jet Li fights and i have adored chinese 'fantasy' ever since i watched an animated series about the monkey king as a kid.<br>
I love both films, but 'Hero' gets my vote because while both are pieces of art, 'Hero' is something i would gladly decorate my apartment with if that makes sense hehe.<br>
Most memorable fights: The gambling hall fight and the authumn forest scene. They make you dream in colours...and sound. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Western:<br>
